## EMERGENCY TROUBLESHOOTING

### **CHECKPOINT FAILURE PROTOCOLS**

**If Checkpoint 1 fails:**
- Re-extract requirements systematically
- Verify age group selection is specific
- Confirm template format is loaded
- Start over if requirements unclear

**If Checkpoint 2 fails:**
- Recount planned errors (must be exactly 10)
- Verify distribution adds up correctly
- Adjust error concepts if age-inappropriate
- Complete planning before content generation

**If Checkpoint 3 fails:**
- Count embedded errors carefully
- Check each content section for correct distribution
- Re-embed missing errors in correct sections
- Verify content length meets age parameters

**If Checkpoint 4 fails:**
- Apply exact template format for all errors
- Quote exact text from training article
- Add missing discussion prompts
- Verify all 10 errors addressed

**If Checkpoint 5 fails:**
- Review entire checklist systematically
- Fix any incomplete elements
- Verify both artifacts are complete
- Do not proceed to publication until all items checked

